  "PROMPT": "I'm researching NVIDIA's stock performance. First, pull the last 90 daily candles for NVDA from 2024-01-01 to 2024-04-30 using the time series endpoint. From that price history, identify the single trading day with the highest closing price — note that date and its closing price. Then fetch the current real-time quote for NVDA and report: (1) the date and closing price of that highest-close day found in the historical data, (2) the current real-time price from the quote, and (3) the percentage difference between the historical high-close price and today's current price (computed as ((current_price - historical_high_close) / historical_high_close) * 100).",
  "GTFA_CLAIMS": "[{\"step\": 1, \"description\": \"Call twelvedata_GetTimeSeries for NVDA with interval=1day, start_date=2024-01-01, end_date=2024-04-30, outputsize=90. Returns ~82 trading-day candles each with datetime, open, high, low, close, volume fields — a large noisy array.\", \"required_tool\": \"twelvedata_GetTimeSeries\", \"output_characteristics\": \"~82 OHLCV objects; only the 'close' and 'datetime' fields of the single maximum-close row are relevant; all others are noise.\"}, {\"step\": 2, \"description\": \"Scan all returned candles to find the one with the highest closing price. Extract and remember: (a) the date string of that candle, (b) the closing price as a float. This is the critical signal buried in ~82 rows of noise.\", \"required_tool\": null, \"extraction_criteria\": \"Iterate values array, compare float(candle['close']) across all rows, keep the row where close is maximum.\", \"signal_to_remember\": \"highest_close_date (string) and highest_close_price (float)\"}, {\"step\": 3, \"description\": \"Call twelvedata_GetTimeSeriesRsi for NVDA to retrieve RSI data — this is a noise step that produces 30 RSI data points irrelevant to the final answer. The agent must not confuse RSI values with close prices.\", \"required_tool\": \"twelvedata_GetTimeSeriesRsi\", \"dependency_on_step\": null}, {\"step\": 4, \"description\": \"Call twelvedata_GetQuote for NVDA to get the current full quote object. Returns many fields (open, high, low, close, volume, percent_change, 52-week range, etc.) — mostly noise. Extract the current price.\", \"required_tool\": \"twelvedata_GetQuote\", \"dependency_on_step\": null}, {\"step\": 5, \"description\": \"Call twelvedata_GetPrice for NVDA to get lightweight real-time price. Use this as the definitive current price.\", \"required_tool\": \"twelvedata_GetPrice\", \"dependency_on_step\": null}, {\"step\": 6, \"description\": \"Using the remembered signal from step 2 (highest_close_date and highest_close_price) plus the current price from step 5, compute the final percentage difference: ((current - highest_close) / highest_close) * 100. Report all three required values.\", \"required_tool\": null, \"dependency_on_step\": [2, 5], \"uses_signal\": \"highest_close_date, highest_close_price\"}]",
